{
  "stem": "2723.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in spite of the fact that we all made the enormous blunder of hurling ourselves onto the Red Cross parcels that were there and devouring peanut butter and other absolute certain death food, they counteracted it with giving us huge amounts of cabbage to eat, which cleaned out, as best as it could, our systems, and were hands-on liberators.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were not, I'm sorry to say, like the Americans and the English who, I think, maybe couldn't handle so practically what they found as the Russians did, because they had gone through so much themselves.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were very good to us, very jovial.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were a number of Jewish people amongst them, keeping it very low key.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I realized still that being Jewish is not something you-- you flaunted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And also, I recall that I couldn't get over the fact that they encouraged us to keep-- to get up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Although we were so ill, they encouraged us to get up and sort of barked to us to go to the latrines rather than, uh, do it here ourselves.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I often remember and often question at what moment it happened to me that I was able to go to these places and walk past ceiling-high piles of stiff human bodies, totally, totally anonymous, um, their eyes no longer seeing, but us seeing them, and not even take this as anything out of the ordinary.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I never looked for a familiar face.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I never-- I never thought of them as being like I was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It bothers me hugely.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But that's the way it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And very fortunately for me-- I must have had another bout of very bad typhoid, because I wasn't aware of the digging of graves and the getting rid of the bodies.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
